@NODE INTRO "Introduction"
@{u}ARW's Magic Icons V2.1@{uu}

     Here is my second(.one) MagicWB icon collection.  These icons are
     mostly original, but some are modified (and improved I think :-) from
     other MagicWB icons and other 'standard' icons (isn't MagicWB
     standard by now? :-).  I have also included some of the better icons
     from AWMWB1, such as the non-lace disk icons, probably the most
     useful in the collection.

     All icons are standard size so you don't have to have an uneven
     display if you don't want to.

     All the drawer icons have empty drawers behind them, so you can
     use IconUpdate or similar program to update your old drawers.
	 @{i}Please keep this archive intact, or make sure you use the
	 -e option in LHA to repack them, otherwise the empty drawers
	 will be lost.@{ui}

     There are also some icons designed for non-interlaced displays.
     The only MWB icons that don't look right on non-interlaced displays
     are the disk ones I feel, so I've designed these so they look a
     bit better and take up less space.  I've seen SmallMWB or what
     ever it is, and quite frankly the icons in it suck.

     I also don't include any pics of my WB in archives either -
     it only horrendously increases the size of the archive, and I don't
     honestly think it interests people that much.

     @{b}Note@{ub} - These icons are designed for MagicWB2 or above,
     running MagicWBDaemon or a similar utility.  Otherwise
     they may look a bit wierd on your WB depending on how many
     colours you are using.
@ENDNODE
