     RAM -          A smaller RAM icon for non-laced displays.

     Network -      Same size as hard disk icon.

     Cartridge -    Correct size cartridge icon.

     The below icons are for use with NewIcons' DefIcons utility.  DefIcons
     lets you define def_icons for all file systems, so you get a real
     icon for your PC, Mac or CD disks.  Also useful is MultiFileSystem.
     This utility 'combines' all your file systems into one, meaning
     that only one disk icon ever comes up.  e.g. you don't get DF0:????
     or PC0:???? icons when an disk with the other filesystem is
     inserted.  Remember not to install the whole NewIcons package,
     it contains inferior icons :-)

     Plenty of MagicWB def icons for all sorts of files are available
     primarily in JTEMWB4.lha in pic/icon on Aminet, with a couple
     also in JTEMWB3.lha and from RomIcons4.lha onwards.

     Both NewIcons and MultiFileSystem are by Nicola Salmoria, and are
     both available on Aminet (util/wb/NewIcons.lha) and I forget the
     exact name of MFS, but it is something like util/wb/MFS20.lha,
     but don't quote me on that, it might not even be in that file
     area (wow, that paragraph rambled a bit, didn't it? :-)

     All the icons below are originally by @{b}Rom@{ub}, I've just
     corrected the aspect ratio for non-lace displays.  If you would
     like the original icons, they are in RomIcons8.lha, in pic/icon
     on Aminet.

     def_CDDAdisk - for CDs.

     def_MSD0disk - for CrossDOS PC disks (Windoze logo on black disk).

     def_MAC0disk - for Macs (Apple logo on grey disk).

     def_MAC1disk - for Macs (Apple logo on light blue disk).

@ENDNODE
